df <- readRDS(here("data", "STU_QQQ_5.rds"))
df %>% head()
library(janitor)
df %>% 
  filter(CNT == "IRL") %>% 
  # haven::as_factor() %>% # changes to its value
  remove_empty() %>% # rows and columns
  remove_constant() -> dfI
value for "which" not specified, defaulting to c("rows", "cols")
filter: removed 606,427 rows (99%), 5,577 rows remaining
dfI
options(scipen = 999)
dfI %>% 
  summarise(across(where(is.labelled), \(x) attributes(x)$label)) %>% 
  tidylog::pivot_longer(everything(), names_to = "Column", values_to = "Description") %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(Type = sapply(Column, \(x) class(df[[x]])[3])) %>% 
  mutate(First_5_Values = sapply(Column, \(x) paste(head(na.omit(df[[x]]), 5) , collapse = ", "))) %>%
  mutate(naPercent = sapply(Column, \(x) dfI %>% zap_labels() %>% .[[x]] %>% is.na() %>% mean %>% "*"(100) %>% round(2))) -> dfI.desc
summarise: now one row and 82 columns, ungrouped
pivot_longer: reorganized (SOCONPA, BODYIMA, JOYREADP, PRESUPP, PASCHPOL, …) into (Column, Description) [was 1x82, now 82x2]
mutate: new variable 'Type' (character) with 2 unique values and 0% NA
mutate: new variable 'First_5_Values' (character) with 80 unique values and 0% NA
mutate: new variable 'naPercent' (double) with 70 unique values and 0% NA
